The paper proposes a neural architecture to learn the construction of placement delivery arrays (PDAs) for coded caching, which is a technique used in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed model uses mechanisms of neural attention and reinforcement learning, which are common in deep learning and machine learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a sequence-to-sequence model, which is a common technique in natural language processing, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with network optimization, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
